    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="401"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.00/1393.</note>
                <head>[Extract]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 44.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the national
                    elections were held in this country on Sunday, Monday, and Tuesday, the 29th to
                    31st ultimo, inclusive. Gen. Manuel Bonilla and Dr. Francisco Bográn are
                    declared to have been chosen President and Vice President, respectively.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles D. White.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
